SEARCH

All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AlternateIndexBuilder
An alternative to the class IndexBuilder, instead of building an index that excludes common words the index is of their occurrences in the text only.
IndexBuilder
The class IndexBuilder builds and outputs an index from a text, each word has an associated definition and page index.
Indexer
The Interface Indexer is an abstract blueprint of an index.
IndexSetup
The class IndexSetup is an abstract class that contains instance variable setter methods for any class extending it and acts as a superclass for that class.
Menu
Menu is a command line User Interface for the application, it presents a menu with multiple options for setting file locations, building an index, actions upon that index and quitting the application.
Parser
The interface Parser is an abstract parser that has one single abstract method (SAM) that must be implemented by any class using this interface.
ProgressBar
The interface ProgressBar contains one method that prints a progress bar to the console.
Runner
The class Runner contains the main method of the application, it creates a new instance of Menu and begins it operation.
WordDetail
The class WordDetail associates a word with a definition and the pages it occurs on.
